Vestiture. Scape with bristles as long as scape diameter, those on apical half slightly longer, ca. 1.2 x scape diameter; apex of scape with some recurved bristles; on pedicel and fl. 1 some longer bristles, 1.5 x fl. 3 diameter, on fl. 2 and fl. 3 little shorter than fl. 3 diameter (
Fig. 6
), and on remaining flagellomeres, ca. 0.5 x fl. 3 diameter. Other characteristics of the pilosity as described for the genus.

Geographical distribution. Apparently it is an endemic species from the north of Amazon basin (biogeographical component NAm, see
Camargo & Pedro 2003
).
